race.description: All Torque Engineering Mandurah Cup H
race.comment: OUR OZZIE SALUTE (5) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 0.8 lengths at Cannington in a handy 29.80 beating Silent Assassin. Has a tricky draw to overcome but goes well over this trip. Hard to fault his recent form and can win again. IMPRESS HAWKINS (2) goes very well at the course with six wins and a placing from 12 starts. Scored by 0.8 lengths last time (30.04) in a Grade 5 over 520m at Cannington. Can feature with the right run. SHEPHERD'S WAY (1) is a well performed dog and winner of 10 races who is worth forgiving after finishing out of the placings at this track (28.09). Comes out of a solid form race last start. Should be thereabouts. SPENCER (4) has claims fresh from a recent placing.
